        <atom:modified>Mon, 20 Mar 2023 13:53:00 +0000</atom:modified>
        <guid>http://localhost:1313/RantsAndRaves/posts/2023/03/fixing-lyx-for-hidpi-monitor/</guid>
        <description>My new laptop has a 4K monitor and my tool of choice for writing my Arduino books, Lyx, always displayed the toolbar icons as &amp;ldquo;so very tiny, it is hard to see the damned things!&amp;rdquo;
After much experimenting with the monitor&amp;rsquo;s scaling, fractional scaling and such like, I found QT_AUTO_SCREEN_SCALE_FACTOR which should fix things.
I tested:
1 2 export QT_AUTO_SCREEN_SCALE_FACTOR=1 lyx &amp;amp; and yes, the icons were now usable. Hooray. I just need to make this permanent.</description>
        
